</p>
</div>

Gmail Classifier is a full-stack web application designed to help users categorize their Gmail emails efficiently. It fetches emails in real-time, allows users to create custom categories based on keywords, and provides a clean interface for managing and viewing classified emails.

âœ¨ Key Features
ğŸ” Secure Google OAuth 2.0: Log in securely with your Google account to grant read-only access to your Gmail.

ğŸ”„ Real-Time Email Sync: The backend polls your Gmail and pushes updates to the frontend instantly using Socket.IO.

ğŸ“‚ Custom Categorization: Create, edit, and delete custom categories with specific keywords for automatic email filtering.

ğŸ” Dynamic Filtering & Search: Instantly search emails by subject, sender, or content and filter by your custom categories.

ğŸ³ Dockerized Environment: A consistent, simple setup for both frontend and backend services with a single command.

ğŸ’» Modern Tech Stack: Built with a robust MERN-style stack and enhanced with TypeScript, Vite, and Tailwind CSS.

ğŸš€ Future Enhancements: NLP Classification
The next major feature planned for this project is the integration of a Natural Language Processing (NLP) model.

ğŸ§  Automatic Classification: A machine learning model will analyze email content and context to automatically assign it to the most relevant category (e.g., "Promotions," "Social," "Work," "Urgent").

ğŸ’¡ Smarter Suggestions: The system will learn from user actions to improve its accuracy and suggest new keywords for your categories.

ğŸ› ï¸ Tech Stack
The application is built with a modern, full-stack JavaScript/TypeScript toolchain.

